  "prompt": "What should I do if I graduated from uni 11 years ago and had only found work two years after for only a few months?",
  "response": "If you've been struggling with employment after graduation, here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Skills and Resume Improvement\n- Update your resume\n- Take online courses or certifications\n- Learn new in-demand skills\n- Consider professional development programs\n\n2. Job Search Strategies\n- Network extensively\n- Use job search websites\n- Attend job fairs\n- Leverage LinkedIn\n- Consider recruitment agencies\n\n3. Career Exploration\n- Evaluate your career goals\n- Research growing industries\n- Consider career counseling\n- Look into transferable skills\n- Be open to different job types\n\n4. Practical Steps\n- Consider internships or volunteer work\n- Look for entry-level positions\n- Be willing to start in lower positions\n- Consider part-time or freelance work\n- Gain practical experience\n\n5. Address Employment Gaps\n- Be honest about your employment history\n- Explain what you've been doing during gaps\n- Highlight any skills learned during that time\n- Show willingness to learn and grow\n\n6. Mental Health and Support\n- Seek support from family/friends\n- Consider career coaching\n- Stay positive and persistent\n- Manage stress and maintain confidence\n\nRemember, it's never too late to restart your career. Focus on continuous learning and remain adaptable.",
